	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Cape Town - A search for a light aircraft that went missing between Wonderboom Airport and Middelburg in Mpumalanga was underway on Saturday. Air Traffic Navigation Services spokesperson Percy Morokane confirmed that an aircraft was reported missing, and said a search and rescue operation had been activated. Further details were not immediately available, but earlier Twitter's @crimeairnetwork said the craft was a Beechcraft Bonanza. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  